I just want to clarify the final point between opportunity loss vs capital
loss. In March 2009 when fully invested, the choice I would have had is either
a) sell something I had bought few months earlier at a loss to buy something I
like better now or b) forgo the stock that I really liked given the new
opportunity. Maybe that's an easier choice when you have obvious losers.

I agree with you that you can't time the market and that's the last thing I'm
trying to do, but opportunity cost is not timing it but seeing something that
is even more misvalued (either on the up or down) - otherwise the moment you
become fully invested you've already called the bottom, hence you are playing
the lottery that you've already had your best shot.
